title: For Sale:  German WWII k98 Mauser bcd 42 Most Numbers Match
postcontent: For sale, German WWII k98 Mauser rifle marked “bcd 42” manufactured at the Wilhelm-Gustloff-Werke, Weimar in 1942. Stock is not original to the rifle, it is a late 1944 - early 1945 semi kriegsmodell but the handguard is matched to the rifle and has the same serial number as the rifle does. There are no RC or Yugo stamps on the rifle or the stock. There is a very light import stamp on the keel of the barrel towards the front sight. Very difficult to make out the importer. All visible numbers on metal parts match, except for number on the butt plate. Receiver, rear sight parts, trigger guard, handguard, front bands all match, floor plate has no markings or number. The bolt does not have a serial number on it, not sure if it was issued this way or it was removed, however the bolt does have an “eagle ‘1’ “ stamp on both the receiver and a “1” on the underside of the bolt, so the bolt is definitely Gustloff Werke manufacture and is correct for the rifle, if it were issued without a serial number, which did happen on occasion. All waffenamt eagles have been cleanly peened out, following the outline of the eagles. Bore is very good – excellent, good rifling, not a rotted out sewer pipe like most. Stock has a repair on the keel towards the rear. E-mail me for additional pictures. Selling for $750.00, FTF Frisco, Texas, cash only, no trades. Will ship to FFL or C&R, must be able to accept from non FFL individual, US Postal Money Order only, buyer pays for shipping and insurance and all FFL and transfer costs and fees.
